item.description:
## Place, Modify, Batch and Cancel Orders on the account WebSocket

You can now place, modify and cancel orders on the `account` WebSocket.

Valid types are `PLACE_LIMIT_ORDER`, `PLACE_MARKET_ORDER`, `MODIFY_ORDER`, `BATCH_ORDERS` and `CANCEL_LIMIT_ORDER`.

Please note that `price` and `quantity` should be provided as strings as shown in the sample requests below.

The "payload" portion of the JSON body supports all the same fields as the HTTP request body for the relevant order type.

To maintain a clear link between requests and responses, embed a `clientMsgId` within your request data. This ID will be present in the returned responses that are associated with WebSocket requests as seen below.

### PLACE_LIMIT_ORDER

Sample WS request:

``` json
{
  "type": "PLACE_LIMIT_ORDER",
  "clientMsgId": "123456789abcd",
  "payload": {
    "side": "BUY",
    "quantity": "0.0001",
    "price": "300000",
    "pair": "BTCUSDT",
    "postOnly": true,
    "reduceOnly": false,
    "customerOrderId": "WS-JSON-2933586967831375",
    "timeInForce": "GTC",
    "allowMargin": false,
    "postOnlyReprice": false
  }
}
//Sample message feed for a successful response:
{
  "type": "PLACE_LIMIT_WS_RESPONSE",
  "data": {
    "orderId": "22e5aa28-f52b-46ba-811e-5052fd2c7289",
    "customerOrderId": "WS-JSON-2933586967831375"
  },
  "clientMsgId": "123456789abcd"
}
// Sample message feed when request exceeds rate limit
{
  "type": "RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED",
  "data": {
    "requestType": "PLACE_LIMIT_ORDER"
  },
  "clientMsgId": "123456789abcd"
}

 ```

---

### PLACE_MARKET_ORDER

Sample WS request:

``` json
{
  "type": "PLACE_MARKET_ORDER",
  "clientMsgId": "123456789abcd",
  "payload": {
    "side": "BUY",
    "baseAmount": "0.0001",
    "pair": "BTCUSDT",
    "customerOrderId": "WS-JSON-2933586967831375",
    "allowMargin": false
  }
}
//Sample message feed for a successful response:
{
  "type": "PLACE_MARKET_WS_RESPONSE",
  "data": {
    "orderId": "22e5aa28-f52b-46ba-811e-5052fd2c7289",
    "customerOrderId": "WS-JSON-2933586967831375"
  }
  "clientMsgId": "123456789abcd"
}
// Sample message feed when request exceeds rate limit
{
  "type": "RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED",
  "data": {
    "requestType": "PLACE_MARKET_ORDER"
  }
  "clientMsgId": "123456789abcd"
}

 ```

---

### BATCH_ORDERS

Please note that when sending a Batch Order the type field may contain the following: `PLACE_LIMIT`, `PLACE_MARKET`, `MODIFY_ORDER`, and `CANCEL_ORDER`.

Sample WS request:

``` json
{
  "type": "BATCH_ORDERS",
  "clientMsgId": "123456789abcd",
  "payload": {
    "requests": [
      {
        "type": "PLACE_LIMIT",
        "data": {
          "pair": "BTCUSDC",
          "side": "SELL",
          "quantity": "0.0021",
          "price": "60000",
          "timeInForce": "GTC"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "PLACE_MARKET",
        "data": {
          "pair": "BTCUSDT",
          "side": "SELL",
          "quoteAmount": "10",
          "timeInForce": "GTC"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "PLACE_MARKET",
        "data": {
          "pair": "BTCUSDT",
          "side": "SELL",
          "baseAmount": "0.0001",
          "timeInForce": "GTC"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "MODIFY_ORDER",
        "data": {
          "customerOrderId": "WS-JSON-2938586967831375",
          "pair": "BTCUSDT",
          "newRemainingQuantity": "0.0001",
          "newPrice": "1870000",
          "modifyMatchStrategy": "RETAIN_ORIGINAL"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "CANCEL_ORDER",
        "data": {
          "customerOrderId": "WS-JSON-2938586967831375",
          "pair": "BTCUSDT"
        }
      }
    ]
  }
}
// Sample message feed when request exceeds rate limit
{
  "type": "RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED",
  "data": {
    "requestType": "BATCH_ORDERS"
  }
  "clientMsgId": "123456789abcd"
}

 ```

---

